    "title": "Rising rates and a defaulting industrial",
    "description": "Three rounds. Rates grind higher while an industrial name (Acme) deteriorates and finally defaults, and a strong technology name (Globex) stays healthy. Approving Acme's payer swap without collateral leaves a real closeout loss when it defaults; requiring collateral removes it. Teaches why collateral terms decide the consequence, not the trade economics.",
    "n_rounds": 3,
    "learning_objectives": [
      "See how a payer swap moves into the money as rates rise.",
      "Watch a counterparty's CVA climb as its credit deteriorates.",
      "Feel the closeout loss on an under-collateralized book at default.",
      "Compare that loss against a collateralized book with the same trade."
    ]
  },
